<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Schema-accurate DrugBank XML test fixture (T1).

  This fixture is deliberately minimal but mirrors the real DrugBank 5.x
  XML structure documented at https://docs.drugbank.com/xml. It exercises
  every XPath branch in DrugBankPipeline._parse_drug_element /
  _extract_properties / _extract_interactors:

  1. DB00645 - approved small-molecule drug (Aspirin-like).
  2. DB00463 - Baycol (cerivastatin) - WITHDRAWN killer drug, retains
     the 'approved' tag. Must come out is_fda_approved=False (S3).
  3. DB00011 - insulin-like biologic - NO InChIKey, NO SMILES. Must
     get a SYNTH-DB00011 key (S7). Must NOT be dropped.
  4. DB00001 - drug with BOTH target AND enzyme on same UniProt ID
     P00734 (thrombin). source_id must be distinct (S22).
  5. DB00002 - drug with multi-action target (agonist|positive
     modulator). Both actions captured (S2, S10).
  6. DB00003 - drug with non-human (E. coli) target. Must be filtered
     by default organism=Humans config (S9).
  7. DB00004 - drug with experimental MW="180.16 g/mol" (units in
     value). MW must parse as 180.16 float (S11). Also has calculated
     MW=180.15 - experimental wins (S18).
  8. DB00005 - drug with <mechanism-of-action> containing <paragraph>
     children. All text captured (S4).
  9. DBXXXX - drug with invalid DrugBank ID format (not DB\d{5}).
     Must be skipped (DQ4).
 10. DB00006 - drug with no <drugbank-id primary="true">. Must fall
     back to first drugbank-id (DQ5 partial coverage).
 11. DB00007 - drug with <name>A</name> (1 char). Must be renamed to
     Unknown-DB00007 (DQ3).
 12. DB00008 - drug with MW=-50 (impossible). Must be set to None (DQ2).
-->
